nal AI service is needed. Exercise the auto-configuration with ApplicationContextRunner and a local stub ChatModel bean. For 2.0.0, ChatClientBuilderProperties.ToolCalling exposes enabled and advisorOrder only; do not use the removed stream-tool-call-responses property or isStreamToolCallResponses() accessor.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The existing RC2 test pins Spring AI and Spring Boot support dependencies to RC versions; mixing those with the 2.0.0 artifact caused the observed javac failure.\",\n    \"Adding micrometer-tracing is optional and changes which observation nested configuration activates; do not add it unless the generated tests intentionally cover the tracer-present branch.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_089e898098dc44c9016a406d33e3648197a2f2268d0b83fff4\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 831, "output": 1008, "cacheRead": 43008, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 44847, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782607144808, "responseId": "resp_089e898098dc44c9016a406d294c608197a6794b118a736436"}}
