ional; it's necessary for the ApplicationContextRunner. I also want to make sure to specify that there’s no Docker or environmental properties involved. I need a clear summary without restating dependencies but mentioning the need for local setups and avoiding certain properties.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"The artifact is a Spring Boot auto-configuration module whose main collaborators are optional Maven dependencies, so the normal scaffold cannot reach meaningful ChatClient auto-configuration coverage without adding them explicitly.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.springframework.ai:spring-ai-client-chat:2.0.0\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"Provides ChatClient, ChatModel, advisors, prompt/message types, and observation handler classes used by ChatClientAutoConfiguration.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.springframework.ai:spring-ai-autoconfigure-model-tool:2.0.0\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"Provides ToolCallingAutoConfiguration and tool-calling auto-configuration types referenced by the chat client auto-configuration.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-autoconfigure:4.1.0\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"Provides Spring Boot auto-configuration annotations and AutoConfigurations support needed to load and exercise the module.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-test:4.1.0\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"Provides ApplicationContextRunner, the normal lightweight way to test this auto-configuration without a full application.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"No Docker image, API key, or external AI service is needed. Exercise the auto-configuration with ApplicationContextRunner and a local stub ChatModel bean. For 2.0.0, ChatClientBuilderProperties.ToolCalling exposes enabled and advisorOrder only; do not use the removed stream-tool-call-responses property or isStreamToolCallResponses() accessor.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The existing RC2 test pins Spring AI and Spring Boot support dependencies to RC versions; mixing those with the 2.0.0 artifact caused the observed javac failure.\",\n    \"Adding micrometer-tracing is optional and changes which observation nested configuration activates; do not add it unless the generated tests intentionally cover the tracer-present branch.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_089e898098dc44c9016a406d33e3648197a2f2268d0b83fff4\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 831, "output": 1008, "cacheRead": 43008, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 44847, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782607144808, "responseId": "resp_089e898098dc44c9016a406d294c608197a6794b118a736436"}, "toolResults": []}
